<body>
    <div class="container mt-4">
        <h1 class="text-center">Solar Panels Information</h1>

        <!-- Carousel -->
        <div id="solarPanelCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-bs-ride="carousel" data-bs-interval="3000">
            <div class="carousel-inner">
                <div class="carousel-item active">
                    <img src="~/Images/DifferentSolarPanels.png" class="d-block w-100" alt="Different Solar Panels">
                </div>
                <div class="carousel-item">
                    <img src="~/Images/MonocrystallineSolarPanel.jpg" class="d-block w-100" alt="Monocrystalline Solar Panels">
                </div>
                <div class="carousel-item">
                    <img src="~/Images/PolycrystallineSolarPanel.jpg" class="d-block w-100" alt="Polycrystalline Solar Panels">
                </div>
                <div class="carousel-item">
                    <img src="~/Images/ThinFilmSolarPanel.jpg" class="d-block w-100" alt="Thin-Film Solar Panels">
                </div>
            </div>
            <button class="carousel-control-prev" type="button" data-bs-target="#solarPanelCarousel" data-bs-slide="prev">
                <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon"></span>
            </button>
            <button class="carousel-control-next" type="button" data-bs-target="#solarPanelCarousel" data-bs-slide="next">
                <span class="carousel-control-next-icon"></span>
            </button>
        </div>

        <!-- Solar Panel Information Sections -->
        <div class="row mt-4">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card p-3">
                    <h2>Monocrystalline</h2>
                    <p>These panels are the most efficient and long-lasting, ideal for small spaces. They have a sleek black design and perform well even in low sunlight.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card p-3">
                    <h2>Polycrystalline</h2>
                    <p>A more affordable option, but slightly less efficient than monocrystalline. These panels have a blueish tint and are great for larger spaces where cost is a factor.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card p-3">
                    <h2>Thin-Film</h2>
                    <p>Lightweight and flexible, making them ideal for commercial use. They can be installed on curved surfaces and work well in diffused light conditions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Maintenance and Installation -->
        <div class="mt-4">
            <h2>Maintenance and Installation</h2>
            <p>Solar panels require minimal maintenance, but regular cleaning (every 6 months) helps maintain efficiency. Dust, leaves, and bird droppings can reduce performance.</p>
            <p>Installation should be done by certified professionals to ensure safety and efficiency. The process involves mounting the panels, connecting them to an inverter, and linking to the electricity grid or a battery system.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Brands and Cost -->
        <div class="mt-4">
            <h2>Popular Brands and Cost</h2>
            <p>Top brands in the UK include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Tesla Solar</strong> - Known for advanced technology and battery storage solutions.</li>
                <li><strong>SunPower</strong> - Offers some of the highest efficiency panels on the market.</li>
                <li><strong>LG Solar</strong> - High-quality panels with long warranties.</li>
                <li><strong>Jinko Solar</strong> - Affordable and reliable panels for residential and commercial use.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Costs:</strong> Prices for a full system (including installation) range from:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Small home system (3kW) - £3,000 to £5,000</li>
                <li>Medium home system (4kW) - £5,000 to £7,000</li>
                <li>Large home system (6kW+) - £7,000 to £10,000</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Government grants and incentives, such as the Smart Export Guarantee (SEG), can help reduce costs.</p>
        </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
